description:
secretx-systemd/src/lib.rs:62-93 — the doc-comment on `from_uri` says only:

    /// # Errors
    ///
    /// Returns [`SecretError::InvalidUri`] if the backend is not `systemd`,
    /// the credential name is empty, or contains `/` (path traversal).

It does not state which credential names are accepted, which is the operative question for callers.

Add a sentence describing the rule (to be aligned with the systemd-creds rule fix in 0hfd.1):

  'The credential name must satisfy systemd's credential_name_valid() rule: non-empty, not '.' or '..', no '/', no ':', no bytes < 0x20 or >= 0x7F, length <= 255 bytes. See systemd src/shared/creds-util.c:46.'

This documents the bus-factor invariant — a contributor in 12 months can verify the validator still matches systemd's source without rediscovering the rule.
